namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

transcript.text: Hello welcome to on print shop.
This video is about how to add offline orders.
So offline order is the order which you can add from the admin side on behalf of your customer.

If in some cases your customer gives you order over phone call, e-mail, WhatsApp or any other media, it helps to centralized your all orders at one place and it helps to generate the reports, order tracking and maintain the order delivery date.
Let's see how to add offline order from the admin side.
Just go to the admin, go to orders, here is the button Add new order.
So there are three easy steps.
The step one is to select customer.
Step 2, choose product, step three, payment and shipping.
So in the very first step, step one, choose customer.
So if customer is already registered in your website, then you just need to put the name over here.
So it will be visible directly over here.
You can see it over here.
And if the customer is not registered or it's a new customer, in that case you need to click on add customer button here.
You just need to provide all the details and save it.
That's it.
So as you will select the customer you can see all the details.
Customer details will be over here.
Then we just need to click on next button here we need to provide the product details.
So there are two kind of product one is existing and the second is custom product.
Existing means the product which are available on your website for sale.
Custom product means the product which are not listed on your website.
So it's a completely new product which you need to add here from scratch.
So right now we are adding for existing product suppose standard business card.
So as you as we will select the standard business card, it will show all the details.
We can choose different options from here and just click on apply all.
So all these details will be automatically applied over here.
You can see 2 into two quantities.
All the options are available over here.
If anything additional information you want to give, you can do it over here.
Enterprise product price is automatically game.
The product weight is also automatically come production days will if you want to change it, you can change it.
The product SKU artwork name is you can change the artwork name if you have the artwork ready.
In that case you can upload that artwork.
Otherwise you can leave it.
Then the order product status is proof approved or awaiting proof or awaiting artwork.
You can update, then save and add another product.
If you want to add multiple products, you just need to click on this button.
If this is the only one, just click on save and continue.
On this page, you need to select the which shipping method you are going to opt for this client, let's say local pickup for example.
Then payment method, which payment method you are going to add it from here.
Let's say anything, whatever is five OK, the transaction ID, you can keep all the payment details over here.
Then there is order checkout fields.

If you want to provide this checkout fields OK and the order amount if let's say customer wants to you want to take payment from the customer through generating payment request, you can enable this button as well.
So payment request will be generated and customer can make the online payment.
Once you are done with all this stuff then here you can see the card product details, shipping and billing address.
So as you will fill all the details, click on confirm order.
And here the order has been confirmed, you can see the order ID is 1705.
These details, these details, all the details you can see.
So you can easily add order from the admin site.
If you have any queries and concern, please connect with us at support@onprintshop.com.
Thank you.
